  "ergonomics_risks": "Likely to be used with existing support for caret-color animation to improve the behavior of that feature.",
  "wpt": true,
  "wpt_descr": "Parsing test: https://github.com/web-platform-tests/wpt/blob/master/css/css-ui/animation/caret-animation-parsing.html\n\nIt turns out that while caret blinking behavior does seem to be testable, doing so requires changing chrome to re-enable a blinking caret in web_tests, which was disabled many years ago due to the flakiness it caused. Given the cross-browser differences in blink rate testing seems unwise.\n\nUnit tests were used in the implementation.",
